modules.description: Provides geolocation lookups using IP address data, including country and city detection. Operates on strings representing IP addresses and returns structured location data. Used to enhance user tracking and regional content delivery in network applications.

The module provides operations for initializing, managing, and querying a GeoIP database, enabling lookups of geographic data such as country codes and IDs from IP addresses (as strings or int32) or hostnames, with support for both IPv4 and IPv6. It works with database handles, IP address representations, and hostname inputs, offering functions to configure metadata, character sets, and database availability checks. Use cases include determining geographic origins of network traffic or user locations based on IP or hostname inputs.
